body: While you're not wrong about the paranoia, Russia legalised homosexuality after the October revolution and criminalised it again shortly before Stalin came to power. Idealism isn't the same as holding power. While the first years of the Bolsheviks were heavily idealistic so they could indulge in everyone being "equal" and shit, but when they were attempting to stabilise the country, they realise that the Russian people didn't want gays running around openly being gay so they recriminalised it. The situation they were in changed, it wasn't "magical".
